<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF81FFACF7C026C1FDD0FACF" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF81FFACF7C026C1FDD0FACF" blockId="3.[174,1233,1251,1438]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF81FFACF7C026C1FEA3FB6C" bold="true" box="[227,356,1251,1277]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Posterior notopleural seta black (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF81FFACF42426C6FC43FB6F" box="[775,900,1251,1278]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[344,1061,176,1053]" captionTargetId="figure-208@3.[320,1093,125,1082]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 12–16. C. grandinata. 12 — ♀, habitus, right; 13 — mesonotum, dorsally (SIZK); 14 — wing; 15 — glans; 16 — epandrium (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">fig. 12–13</figureCitation>
), Wing pattern reticulated, with 2 hyaline spots in cell br; apex of r 
<subScript id="BA6F34DEFF81FFACF5562735FD48FAB4" attach="left" box="[629,655,1303,1317]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">2+3</subScript>
with 2 isolated spots, base r 
<subScript id="BA6F34DEFF81FFACF4F02734FC29FAB5" attach="left" box="[979,1006,1302,1316]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">4+5</subScript>
with one oval spot, Stigma with two hyaline spots; apical hyaline spot of triangle small (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF81FFACF4E62706FBD5FAAF" box="[965,1042,1315,1342]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[344,1061,176,1053]" captionTargetId="figure-208@3.[320,1093,125,1082]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 12–16. C. grandinata. 12 — ♀, habitus, right; 13 — mesonotum, dorsally (SIZK); 14 — wing; 15 — glans; 16 — epandrium (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Glans as in 
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF81FFACF38F2706FF0DFACF" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[344,1061,176,1053]" captionTargetId="figure-208@3.[320,1093,125,1082]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 12–16. C. grandinata. 12 — ♀, habitus, right; 13 — mesonotum, dorsally (SIZK); 14 — wing; 15 — glans; 16 — epandrium (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">fig. 15</figureCitation>
and epandrium as in 
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF81FFACF6E92766FDD3FACF" box="[458,532,1348,1374]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1088,1110]" captionTargetBox="[344,1061,176,1053]" captionTargetId="figure-208@3.[320,1093,125,1082]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 12–16. C. grandinata. 12 — ♀, habitus, right; 13 — mesonotum, dorsally (SIZK); 14 — wing; 15 — glans; 16 — epandrium (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">fig. 16</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF81FFACF7C02741FBF9FA0F" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF81FFACF7C02741FBF9FA0F" blockId="3.[174,1233,1251,1438]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF81FFACF7C02741FEB6FAEC" bold="true" box="[227,369,1379,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Comments.</emphasis>
This species occurs throughout the Palaearctic 
<collectingRegion id="E42FF879FF81FFACF4832746FC31FAEF" box="[928,1014,1380,1406]" country="Iraq" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Region</collectingRegion>
, predominantly in the mountain lowlands. Larvae induce galls on shoots of 
<taxonomicName id="E1EB4D18FF81FFACF46B27A6FBE7FA0C" box="[840,1056,1412,1438]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Solidago" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="254" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virgaurea">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF81FFACF46B27A6FBE7FA0C" box="[840,1056,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="254">Solidago virgaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
